How Do Kidney Disease Clinicians View Kidney Supportive Care and Palliative Care? A Qualitative Study.
Kidney clinicians described systemic challenges and compromises in care experiences and the need for development of kidney supportive care services. They expressed that this development would require a consistent and systematic approach that integrates palliative care and embeds kidney supportive care as part of kidney health service delivery.
