    Individuals heterozygous for ALG8 protein-truncating variants are at increased risk of a mild cystic kidney disease. 
ALG8 PTVs were not associated with chronic kidney disease or kidney failure in the MyCode study or the UK Biobank data. Thus, PTVs in ALG8 result in increased risk of a mild cystic kidney disease phenotype.
